      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BERSERKER (1) missed a nose here in a CL4 and was only beaten 1L following behind the progressive Beneficiary over this distance. That's good form and he's going to be tough to beat. NATIVE CLAN (5) finished second behind a dominant winner over 1400m at Launceston but covered the others and will be better for it. Has a small claim and rates to go close. CARNELIAN ROCK (4) is finding it hard to win went well enough two back here over this trip to consider. Better placed today. RICH CLAN (3) was plain at 1600m last time but had been around the mark prior. Better back to this trip freshened, and is in the mix. STEELE MY SUNSHINE (6) is also back in distance and runs along. Gets in light and will be in it a long way.",
